205869660057168.Text: It's baaack!  Voted down only last June by Miami-Dade County's Government Operations Committee, backers of this project must be thinking they finally have the votes to send the SR 836 (also known as the Dolphin Expressway) beyond the county's Urban Development Boundary and out along the edge of the Everglades. A vote and public hearing will take place this Wednesday morning beginning at 9 AM - see location map here: https://goo.gl/maps/225wNdYbqF42   The "Government Center" Metrorail Station will leave you inside the building.  Please try to attend and say NO to this unnecessary and harmful highway expansion.  This issue seems to have united environmentalists from throughout our region who know that new highways in still rapidly-growing South Florida have never alleviated traffic. Instead, expanded highways such as I-595 in Broward County have only facilitated more growth - along with expanded vehicle use.  And as we have pointed out again and again on this Facebook page - South Florida is already reeling under the weight of that development. Our freshwater aquifers are being pumped out to the point where - absent the rare veto from the governor - we almost had a state program to re-inject recycled sewage into our aquifers.  Coastal pollution from wastewater, plus road and agricultural runoff are killing our coastal ecosystems.  And the looming (but very real) threats from sea level rise and coastal flooding, saltwater intrusion into our aquifers, and acidification of our oceans (from excess CO2) round out the environmental nightmare we are creating.  For coastal wildlife which have to live in the runoff we are sending them - their nightmare has long begun.  And for the terrestrial wildlife displaced by our non-stop urban expansion, it is, unfortunately, already too late,    Expected environmental impacts from this particular road expansion include increased sprawl and traffic, endangerment of our underground water supply, paving over and degrading of wetlands and aquifer recharge areas, and threats to badly needed Everglades restoration projects.  More details here:  https://catalystmiami.org/hold-the-line-against-836-expansion/   Please try and join us this Wednesday morning at the county commission meeting.  There are better ways to solve South Florida's transportation crisis than building yet another major highway.  Most metropolitan areas the size of Miami-Dade County have invested heavily in viable mass-transit systems which allow safe, reliable, and rapid access to the entire region.  The Metrorail and Metromover rail lines in the eastern part of Miami-Dade already form a base for that system.  If the goal is removing congestion on area roads, getting drivers out of their cars (instead of onto an expanded highway system) is a much better way to go.

2187725601474898.Text: HUMANISM MANIFESTO   The human development practice of the 20th century, which is the criterion of truth, revealed the utopian nature of communism theory, non-objectively pretended to a more productive method of material and spiritual benefits production which was meant to replace capitalism.   The founders of the communist theory, Karl Marx and Vladimir Lenin, whose theory was the basis of life for half of humanity in the 20th century, believed that capitalistic production method of material and spiritual benefits based on a private property at the expense of production and exploitation of man by man, consciously and necessarily, with the help of the state, proletarian dictatorship would be changed by a more productive communist method based on a public property at the expense of production, via the destruction of a private property in the course of the socialist revolution, which would eliminate the exploitation of man by man.  If, in their view, production methods of material and spiritual benefits, which had preceded the capitalist one, including it, were born in the depths of the historically obsolete preceding production methods, and blindly, by virtue of the objective laws of social development led to their change, so the communist production methods were meant to be established by a forcibly revolutionary way with the help of the state, proletarian dictatorship via the destruction of a private property at the expense of their production and its replacement by a public property.  The essence of the communist theory was set out by Marx in the "Communist Manifesto": "the communists may express their theory via the provision: the destruction of a private property... ".  The communism theory and practice diametrically opposed themselves to the objective laws of the nature and human society development. These laws were discovered by the German philosopher G. Hegel in the 19th century: - unity and struggle (competition) of opposites as a source of nature and society development; - transition of quantitative changes into qualitative ones in nature and society; - the negation of the negation, i.e. the nature and society development on a virtuous circle.  The effect of these laws in nature and society by the followers of Marxism-Leninism, who were dogmatists and did not develop their theory, were incorrectly interpreted and put into practice.  The history of a human society development attests to the fact that social structures are based on the production methods of material and spiritual benefits, following each other in their development process via changing the ownership form on them. They were defined by the influence of the objective developmental laws of nature and society not blindly, but consciously objectively necessarily, i.e. directly proportional to the perception of these laws by humanity and its ability to use them in practice in order to replace its mental and physical labor in the material and spiritual benefits production. Nature, unlike humanity, develops blindly, by virtue of its laws.  So, the initial primitive-communal production method of material and spiritual benefits was founded on such means of production as a spear, a bow and primitive tools with stone tips for bush meat hunting and agriculture. These means belonged to the community. The product was received through the works of the community members using these means and was in the nature of a minimum required product to maintain the life of its members, in view of the low workforce productivity. There was no question of a surplus product that could be possessed and used by the most active and influential members.  A human discovery of copper, iron and a practical ability to use them for the production means of material and spiritual benefits led to the increase in labor productivity and the emergence of a surplus product, which was possessed and used by some of the most active and influential community members. Families, their private property at the expense of the production methods of material and spiritual benefits began to appear, and obtaining, as a result of its usage, material and spiritual benefits. This led to the formation of the state and law as the private property product, for its protection.  These objective laws in the human society evolution were reflected in the work of F.Engels "The Origin of the Family, Private Property and the State".  The primitive communal production method of material and spiritual benefits was replaced by a more productive slaveholding method, however, the necessary and surplus product was created by a human manual labor in its time. As a result of this, a division of labor, merchandise exchange and money circulation emerged and began to develop, as well as the struggle between peoples and states in the form of wars in order to seize their lands and property, hostages and slaves, which had already become a commodity.   As a consequence of the new nature laws discovery and evolutionary development on the basis of production means of material and spiritual benefits in agriculture, cattle breeding and craft, a slaveholding production method of material and spiritual benefits was replaced by a more productive feudal one, based on a private ownership of land holdings with the conversion of slaves into serfs workers.   In the medieval period, when a human being came to know new nature and society laws in mathematics, chemistry, physics and other sciences, as well as learned to obtain and use a thermal and electric energy out of nature substances, create cars and transport in the production process of material and spiritual benefits, which increasingly replaced mental and physical human energy in the production process of material and spiritual benefits. As a result, in the depths of the feudal production method an industry began to emerge and develop and on its material basis the capitalist production method of material and spiritual benefits, as well as commodity exchange and money circulation, based on a private ownership at the expense of material and spiritual benefits production, on the liberation of the serfs and their transformation into wage earners.  What did, in science and philosophy terms, the utopian theory and practice of communism include?  According to this theory, the public ownership production methods of material and spiritual benefits, formed the basis of the communist mode of production, which was to replace a capitalist one, based on a private ownership on them, with an egalitarian distribution of a produced by the workers product and monopoly ownership of the production means of material and spiritual benefits, forcibly removed the objective contradictions between the individual and material interests of workers. But these contradictions, opposites, the struggle of individuals with unequal abilities composed the objective internal original source of a social production development.  In other words, under the enforced equation of the congenitally unequal individuals by the state and monopoly ownership of production means of material and spiritual benefits, the objective preconditions for the action of discovered by G. Hegel laws of nature and society development, including its original source - the law of the unity and struggle of opposites.  Such artificial and utopian model of communist production method was deprived of objective internal sources for its development and was introduced by force, through the revolutionary way and existed with inadequate measures of administrative and criminal enforcement, and naturally, as history has shown, was doomed to destruction.  Mistaking the wish for the reality, his academic and political apologists, the "true successors of the Marxism-Leninism classics " in the 20th century assigned the label "scientific" to the communism theory, which had never happened before in other sciences - mathematics, physics, chemistry, philosophy... Agreeing with the communism founders that politics is the concentrated expression of the economy, i.e. the last was primary, and politics was secondary, they introduced a course of "political economy" to the society, although it was supposed to be about "economic policy".  Considering themselves as materialists, and capitalists as idealists, the communism advocates were idealists, not materialists, and their subordination to the objective laws of social development was recognized by capitalists, who on the contrary were materialists.  Communism, as a theory and historical practice, went down not only due to the theoretical and practical errors, communism died in a naturally historical way. So there is no need to look for guilty ones. That was not so much the fault of its followers, entire nations, generations and their states, as their misfortune. Our grandfathers, fathers, and partly we sacrificed our lives for this; therefore, there is no need to desecrate their historical errors, which were not deprived of historical achievements. Humans are prone to errors, as errors, objectively, are one of understanding way of nature and society laws and their use in practice.  Communist revolutions in the 20th century, set off by the socialist revolution of 1917 in Russia, were utopian, based on the utopian doctrine of communism. The revolutions that accompanied the historical changes of the production methods of material and spiritual benefits, objectively, deliberately necessarily, peacefully or forcibly led to the state power of the owners of their production means. The question naturally arises, in what direction humanity is moving in now?  Having addressed Marx, we see that he divides history into three eras. The first era, including the capitalist one and all preceding production methods, at which the development has the character of a natural historical process, the objective laws of which are not subject to people, Marx calls this the realm of natural necessity. This era, over which the relations of a private property as the blind alienated power dominate, the true realm of freedom opposed to them - the era of humanism.  However, these two eras, two kingdoms, according to Marx, have to be mediated by another intermediate realm, a realm of perceived need - the era of communism.  In K. Marx's opinion "in communism era, a human productive activity is necessary, but increasingly subservient to their will, when freedom is still in the limits of necessity, but the necessity itself is not natural, but perceived, and in this sense passes into freedom. Freedom in that respect can only consist in the fact that the associated manufacturers rationally regulate their metabolism with nature and evolutionarily put it under a total control, instead of dominating them as a blind force. However, this still remains the realm of necessity. Beyond it, the human forces development begins, which is an end in itself, the true realm of freedom, which, however, can flourish only on this realm of necessity as on its basis".  The second half of the 20th century demonstrated in practice the fallacy of this provision, as well as the fallacy of the communism theory. The historical transition from capitalism as a production method of material and spiritual benefits to humanism, as a new production method, which will replace it, will take place not in the utopian communism epoch, but via objectively necessarily evolutionary way in the depth of capitalism, on the basis of discoveries of new nature and society laws and the ability to use them in practice.   In the era of humanism, production means of material and spiritual benefits, created by the human mind and labor, based on the proportionally high enough for this perception level of nature and society laws, by virtue of objective developmental laws of nature and society, used by humanity, will completely replace mental and physical human energy in the production process of material and spiritual benefits. The struggle between people in the course of production process of material and spiritual benefits, private property on them as the primary sources of a social production self-development, market relations, based on the value of the goods will pass out, rather disappear. The state and law, protecting private property on them, will disappear, and they will be replaced by a public sector and moral-ethical rules.  If, prior to the humanism establishment, the basic contradiction underlying the humanity existence and development, was its struggle with the Earth nature to ensure the conditions for its life by its rational, natural metabolism with nature, then in the era of humanism the basic contradiction defining the humanity life and progress, will be its struggle with the infinite in time and space Universe through realizing its laws and using them for this.  In our days a human being is relatively helpless in time and space at the scale of the Universe as he was thousands of years in the past before the Earth nature. A human being can live on the Earth and in the Universe physically and spiritually so long as he deeply perceives the laws of the Earth and Universe and will learn to use them in his everyday life. However, due to the law of relativity, discovered by A. Einstein, and other laws of the Earth and Universe, his life duration in time and space, will be as relatively short as it is nowadays.  The development of humanity, which in the 20th century was drained with 2 world wars, which claimed the lives of tens of millions of people, as well as wasted hundreds of trillions of dollars for the arms race during the 3rd "cold" world war between capitalism and utopian communism objectively sorely fell astern of its current needs due to an insufficient knowledge level of nature and society laws and on this basis creation of the adequate production means of material and spiritual benefits which led to the fact that the conditions of its existence shifted from its rational natural exchange with nature substances to their destruction.   This resulted in a global warming, hundreds of millions of people are starving, and tens of millions are dying of hunger. Such devastating phenomena on a global scale as an armament race, burning trillions of dollars in its firebox, international terrorism, trade and shooting wars between states, ethnic and religious armed conflicts, generating huge waves of migration, drug addiction, and growth of life-threatening diseases follow the life of the humanity.  In our days the global economy, being in the hands of transnational corporations, is experiencing a deep crisis due to abuse of the natural resources rent, de-industrialization in pursuit of super profits in the countries with cheap labor, the gap between labor and capital and between industrial and financial capitals.  Humanity in the form of its individuals, nations and their states develops by virtue of objective laws of nature and society consciously objectively necessarily, directly proportionally to the perception of these laws and its ability to use them in practice. Therefore, competitive struggle, rivalry between them is an objective category of their existence, the source of their development.  In the 21st century, the humanity must join its forces to meet its material needs in energy, through the way of laws perception and thermonuclear fusion mastering, the needs in food products through the way of laws perception and biological synthesis mastering and other reasonably objective requirements, on the basis of perception and mastering of new laws and their use in other areas (semblance of nature) which will lead to the complete replacement of its mental and physical energy, on production means of material and spiritual benefits created by the humanity.  The first sprouts, swallows of a new production method of material and spiritual benefits based on the principles of humanism at the junction of 20th-21st centuries of became the perception and use of the laws in such nature and society areas as the digital electronic computerization, which will be replaced by the digital quantum computerization of the human productive activity and robotization of the latter, which aimed at the replacement of mental and physical human energy in the production process of material and spiritual benefits.  Civic organizations of a human society and moral and ethical rules will replace the state and law evolutionary, consciously, objectively necessarily. In the era of humanism purely human relations between people will be established instead of commodity-money ones, the ideals of Truth, Benefit and Beauty will spring to life.  Nikolai Khandurin, Candidate of Juridical Sciences Kyiv  May 29, 2017.

The reality is that while this plan is not the golden egg to completely solve this problem, it essentially involves baby steps to help a number of families in need.  Many aren't asking for just hands outs, rather they are seeking the opportunity to reinvigorate back into the community. Every member of the council was in favor of the idea, despite the schedule constraints, except for Councilman Michael Perrow, who said the ban sounded like a "one-off enforcement" issue. 546276642434906.Text: We lost one. Are our protections going down the drain?   Quoted in Business Insurance Magazine re the loss of a trans case, EEOC v. Rent-A-Center, in Illinois federal court:   "There were pretty significant differences in testimony about why (Ms. Kerr) was terminated," said Jillian Weiss, a New York-based solo attorney, who represents LGBT people.   "The jury resolved the credibility question in favor of the employer," she said. "It's a signal that transgender people now get to be treated like any other employee" and "juries have a right to believe them or not, and I think that's as fair a result as can be hoped for."   I said this in the context of the  court ruling in this case, prior to trial. The court held that transgender people are protected from sex discrimination. It also ruled there was enough evidence for a reasonable jury to find sex discrimination.   AN EQUAL CHANCE, BUT AT AN UNEQUAL TARGET  Thus, courts, including in the Heartland, understand we're protected under the law. It also means we have an equal chance with everyone else to have our day in court. But for employees, that day is a little bit shorter. The target is a bit farther away.    Statistics show that only about 30% of job discrimination plaintiffs going to trial in federal court win a verdict, as opposed to 45% of plaintiff wins in federal cases generally. That's a huge differential. The deck is stacked against job discrimination plaintiffs across the board, not just LGBTQ employees. Careful and thoughtful curation of cases is important, and even so, it's probably better to settle if you can. Even after a verdict is won, there are appeals, and large verdicts are often pared down a lot. A bad settlement is better than a good judgment.   I don't think LGBTQ job protections are going down the drain. However, I do think we need to strengthen our job discrimination laws generally.   There's speculation in the article that the jury was infected with anti-trans bias. Given the poisonous climate in our country, it's certainly plausible. But I haven't seen any evidence of it in this case yet.     WE STILL HAVE LEGAL PROTECTIONS; LET'S KEEP FIGHTING  I also noted this hopeful point in the article: "There's no indication that I've ever seen that the EEOC is pulling back from its position regarding protection to transgender people from discrimination," said Ms. Weiss.   In fact, I just received word of a victory at the EEOC in one of my cases against a major aerospace defense contractor. Thankfully, the EEOC is an independent commission that doesn't answer directly to the Administration.   While there are many troubling developments in law and politics under the current Administration, we've still got the federal courts. There are about 145 federal judicial vacancies, 19 in the appeals court and 125 in the district court. The Administration has seated 14 appeals court judges and 14 district court judges as of May 2018. Lambda Legal issued a report in December 2017 indicating that it classified about one-third as anti-LGBT. At this rate, it will take them many years to stack the deck against us. At some point, we may need to switch to state courts. Not yet.   The new nominee for EEOC General Counsel, Sharon Fast Gustafson, is troublesome, however. The Leadership Conference on Human and Civil Rights issued a letter stating concerns about her evasive answers on LGBTQ rights.  I'll keep on fighting, and I hope you will too.

That is because it no longer is.  When you call and ask WASPC about this they will tell you that Yakima County Sheriff's office is not currently accredited.  They will also tell you they applied for reaccreditation and prior to the assessment re-contacted WASPC and said they were not going to complete the reaccreditation process.  I was told that I would have to ask the agency whey they did not complete the process. I will try to obtain the information on why they are no longer accredited. I think it is important we all know why the Sheriff's office is no longer a state accredited agency, don't you?  Under my leadership, not only would you know we were seeking reaccreditation, but you would know why it didn't happen or was delayed.  Being totally honest with you though, if the agency had worked hard enough to become accredited, there would be nothing that would keep us from maintaining our accreditation.  Please look over my three main points and keep in mind I bring a leadership style that encompasses all areas of leadership, rather than the thought that I am the next guy up so it falls on me to be the bearer.  I have prepared myself in all areas; experience, education, and training. I can think outside of the box to incorporate different avenues to provide a better service to the valley we all call home.   Public Safety Public Safety in Yakima County is the highest priority of the Sheriff's department. In 2009 when I left the department there were 72 commissioned Deputies.  Currently there are 61 commissioned deputies. Increased Deputies means more patrols and more Deputies available. As Sheriff it will be my primary focus to increase the number of Deputies and improve the safety for all who live in Yakima County.  Interagency Cooperation Working side by side with other law enforcement agencies in the county is imperative.  We not only need to work together we need to train together.  Continuing to work with and build relationships with other law enforcement agencies, our schools, and our citizens through neighborhood watches is necessary for the safety of the people of Yakima County.  As Sheriff I will continue to improve and build on these collaborative relationships.  I look forward to adding SRO's to the rural school districts in the county as well. In order to fight crime within the Yakama Nation it is important to build a relationship with the Yakama Nation government and its people.  People living within the boundaries of the Yakama Nation should be able to call for assistance without the first question they are asked being "are you enrolled".  I envision the Sheriff's office and the Yakama Nation people continuing to grow their relationship so that we can combat crime together within the Nation.  A relationship that ensures all people living within its boundaries live in safety knowing that no matter who they call for help, help will come.  Transparency and Accountability As Sheriff I will be open and accountable to the people of Yakima County. My administration will be transparent in what we do and look to improve all aspects of the service we provide to the people of Yakima County. Continuously working toward being the best law enforcement agency everyone expects to represent Yakima County.
